cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the task of detecting semantic parts of an object in computer vision, which is a core topic in the field of computer vision. The paper proposes an approach that learns from a small training dataset of annotated semantic parts and generalizes to detect semantic parts from a much larger range of viewpoints. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and graphics (cs.GR).
